U.S. Public Pension Funds Return to Hedge Investing, WSJ Reports

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-05-27T05:44:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/u-s-public-pension-funds-return-to-hedge-investing-wsj-reports.html
U.S. public pension funds are putting
more money into  hedge funds  in an attempt to increase long-run
returns, the Wall Street Journal reported.  That makes it possible for them to justify more optimistic
prognoses, the newspaper said.  The Fire & Police Pension Association of  Colorado , for
example, which manages $3.5 billion, has 11 percent of its
portfolio allocated to hedge funds, compared with nothing at the
start of the year, the Journal said, citing Chief Executive
Officer Dan Slack.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
